  {
    "slug": "nothing-headphones",
    "name": "Headphones (1)",
    "brand": "Nothing",
    "category": "audio",
    "externalUrl": "https://intl.nothing.tech/products/headphone-1",
    "availability": "buyable",
    "description": "The Nothing phone is hailed for its instant retro look, and the headphones continue the trend.\n\nAlthough there are new models and cheaper alternatives, the originals have a style all of their own, with tactile controls and a stunning transparent casing.\n\nThe biggest pull for me is the 3.5mm jack, letting you wire these in, a feature missing from many contemporary headphones.\n\nThese headphones, perhaps even more than the Nothing phone, define a counter-culture of tech products, one that defies the trend to homogenise devices and technology so they no longer have a voice.",
    "listingImage": "images/objects/nothing-headphones.webp",
    "detailImage": "images/objects/nothing-headphones-detail.webp"
